name: CNN
text:
Student groups and state politicians are criticizing the University of Georgia for not allowing in-person voting on campus this fall.

Meanwhile, thousands of fans are expected to attend UGA's first home football game on October 3. https://t.co/BzNtWvaUU4

name: CNN
text: Attorney General William Barr told top Justice Department prosecutors that he wants them to be aggressive in bringing charges related to protest violence, including exploring using a rarely used sedition law, a source says https://t.co/G6ynh2KyOm

name: CNN
text: The Democratic Party's grassroots campaign renaissance is facing an existential challenge ahead of the November election, with the sharpest tool in organizers' kits — face-to-face meetings at potential voters' doorsteps — blunted by the Covid-19 pandemic https://t.co/1yAWRH0O5G

name: CNN
text: A 12-foot alligator was spotted in Gulf Shores, Alabama, after Hurricane Sally made landfall early Wednesday. "This is why we don't want to go outside," said Tina Lambert Bennett, who filmed the alligator outside her window. https://t.co/MuzaKk1Icz https://t.co/k3ZkzlEm97

name: CNN
text: DNI Ratcliffe reversed course on his decision to end in-person election security briefings for key members of Congress by announcing that the intelligence community will continue to provide lawmakers on relevant oversight committees with in-person updates https://t.co/L4ss5BfYs3

name: CNN
text: Despite congressional candidate Marjorie Taylor Greene espousing views many see as racist, anti-Semitic and Islamophobic, Republicans are working to bring her into the fold — and insisting they expect her to be a team player if she comes to DC next year https://t.co/vYFd4SN1gi

name: CNN
text: When the pandemic hit the US in March, Imperfect Foods found itself scrambling to keep up with a sudden spike in demand. The online subscription service sells discount "ugly" fruits and vegetables along with staples like baked goods, meat and dairy. https://t.co/nKHLh1hAxE

name: CNN
text: On-time mail service has still not recovered from Postmaster General Louis DeJoy's controversial changes to the US Postal Service as the November election approaches, according to a new report from Senate Democrats https://t.co/F46c4Ecopm

name: CNN
text: US Appeals Court Judge Sandra Lynch pounded lawyers challenging Harvard's affirmative action policies, implicitly disputing their claims of bias against Asian American students and assertions of Supreme Court precedent https://t.co/Fm2XzsOj6o

name: CNN
text: Operation Warp Speed aims to have Covid-19 vaccines moving to administration sites within 24 hours of an FDA license or emergency use authorization, an official said. The aim is to make them free of charge. But supplying and distributing them is complex. https://t.co/QVAdRQomGg
